text: Stella Rose Bennett (born 30 January 2000), known professionally as Benee is a New Zealand singer-songwriter from Grey Lynn, Auckland. She is best known for her songs "Soaked", "Glitter", and "Supalonely" and has released two extended plays Fire on Marazz and Stella & Steve. In 2019, Benee won Best Solo Artist and Best Pop Artist at the New Zealand Music Awards. According to the Straits Times, people like to think of "Supalonely" as a song for the COVID-19 pandemic, even though Benee says she wrote it as a breakup song. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand singer-songwriters Category:Musicians from Auckland Category:Pseudonyms Category:Sopranos Category:People with dyslexia
